03:35.860 --> 03:37.260
Mmm.

03:38.460 --> 03:40.100
This is so good.

03:40.100 --> 03:42.340
I want more.

03:42.340 --> 03:43.820
Don't get greedy.

03:44.860 --> 03:46.220
Jeff?

03:46.220 --> 03:47.940
Hayley.

03:47.940 --> 03:49.300
Sorry.

03:49.300 --> 03:52.340
I was gonna be, like,
so sophisticated when we met.

03:52.340 --> 03:55.780
Little hard to do that with your
mouth full of whatever that is.

03:55.780 --> 03:57.940
It's great. It's great.
Do you want some?

03:57.940 --> 03:59.140
Sure.

04:03.420 --> 04:04.820
Yum.

04:04.820 --> 04:07.220
It's, um...kind of
what I was thinking.

04:07.220 --> 04:08.460
Sorry?

04:10.500 --> 04:11.940
You just don't look like
the kind of guy

04:11.940 --> 04:15.140
who has to meet girls
over the internet.

04:15.140 --> 04:18.500
I think it's better to meet
people online first sometimes.

04:18.500 --> 04:20.500
You get to know
what they're like inside.

04:20.500 --> 04:22.540
When you work as a photographer,
you find out real quick,

04:22.540 --> 04:24.140
people's faces lie.

04:26.780 --> 04:29.140
Does my face lie?

04:30.180 --> 04:33.060
I look at those eyes
and I see...

04:33.060 --> 04:34.580
a girl who reads Zadie Smith,

04:34.580 --> 04:37.180
who listens to John Mayer
and ColdPlay,

04:37.180 --> 04:40.900
who loves Monty Python episodes

04:40.900 --> 04:42.820
and who, desperately,

04:42.820 --> 04:45.860
madly, deeply, wants,

04:45.860 --> 04:49.100
needs, longs for...

04:49.100 --> 04:51.260
more chocolate.

04:53.540 --> 04:55.700
Excellent, excellent
judge of character.

04:58.900 --> 05:01.660
Can I get two of those truffles

05:01.660 --> 05:03.780
and two ganaches?

05:03.780 --> 05:05.660
Now what's a ganache?

05:05.660 --> 05:08.900
You don't know
what a ganache is?

05:08.900 --> 05:11.140
Lucky you're with
a woman of the world

05:11.140 --> 05:13.660
to introduce you
to these things.

05:13.660 --> 05:15.180
And two
chocolate-covered hearts.

05:15.180 --> 05:17.300
And a decaf latte for me.

05:17.300 --> 05:18.580
And...?
I'm good.

05:19.860 --> 05:21.500
Yeah, you do appear so.

05:24.660 --> 05:26.140
So what's in the bag?

05:26.980 --> 05:29.660
Oh, you know, just,
like, books and stuff.

05:29.660 --> 05:31.340
I figured if you stood me up,

05:31.340 --> 05:33.700
then I should have
something to read.

05:33.700 --> 05:36.380
Well...I couldn't really decide.

05:37.940 --> 05:39.540
I'm reading this book
about Jean Seberg.

05:40.580 --> 05:41.980
She's this actress

05:41.980 --> 05:44.300
who slept with all
the wrong people

05:44.300 --> 05:47.260
and ended up killing herself.

05:47.260 --> 05:48.740
Don't you do that.

05:48.740 --> 05:52.220
No. I-I intend to sleep
with all the right people.

05:53.620 --> 05:55.620
Plus, I'm reading
<i>Romeo and Juliet.</i>

05:55.620 --> 05:56.860
It's a ninth grade book,

05:56.860 --> 05:58.740
but I figured
I could have it done

05:58.740 --> 06:00.900
before the school
year starts, so...

06:00.900 --> 06:02.540
Doesn't look like
Elizabethan tragedy.

06:04.340 --> 06:07.500
Oh, ah, no, that's 'cause--

06:07.500 --> 06:09.300
Well, my dad--
he's letting me audit

06:09.300 --> 06:10.780
one of his med
school courses, right?

06:10.780 --> 06:13.060
I don't really understand
half of it,

06:13.060 --> 06:14.580
but I totally love it.

06:14.580 --> 06:16.060
What?

06:16.060 --> 06:17.700
So you go to UCW

06:17.700 --> 06:21.020
and you sit in a lecture hall
with all these grad students

06:21.020 --> 06:23.980
and, what,
do they hit on you?

06:26.100 --> 06:29.020
Why? Are you jealous?
Just admiring.

06:29.020 --> 06:31.860
I didn't know you were interested
in that kind of thing.

06:31.860 --> 06:33.140
What?

06:33.140 --> 06:35.540
You thought since we'd been
chatting for three weeks

06:35.540 --> 06:37.580
that you knew
everything about me?

06:37.580 --> 06:39.940
Plus, they wouldn't hit
on a 14-year-old girl.

06:39.940 --> 06:43.060
They're, like, old enough
to be my dad, so...

06:44.180 --> 06:45.940
They're like...

06:45.940 --> 06:48.420
They're bad older.
They're-- You're not--

06:50.820 --> 06:52.740
I'm so articulate.

06:52.740 --> 06:54.500
Sorry. Can I just,
like, start over?

06:54.500 --> 06:57.820
No. I get it. I get it.
I just thought...

06:57.820 --> 07:00.940
You know, well, you look
older than you are.

07:00.940 --> 07:03.340
You certainly act
older than you are.

07:06.100 --> 07:07.300
Really?

07:07.300 --> 07:11.100
Yeah. I was expecting someone
not as impressive.

07:12.940 --> 07:14.300
Me too.

07:19.860 --> 07:20.980
Cool shirt.

07:20.980 --> 07:22.140
You want it?

07:23.220 --> 07:25.500
No, I didn't really bring
enough bucks, so...

07:25.500 --> 07:27.540
And yet, not actually
what I was asking.

07:27.540 --> 07:28.980
Sure, I want it.

07:28.980 --> 07:32.020
Can I get a green shirt
in a small, please?

07:32.020 --> 07:33.500
No. No, no.

07:33.500 --> 07:35.500
I can't let you do that.
What? Because--

07:35.500 --> 07:37.260
Because--
What? Because you'd be so

07:37.260 --> 07:38.980
indebted to me
that you'd have to...

07:38.980 --> 07:42.140
Okay. I guess I can
let you do that.

07:42.140 --> 07:43.900
You have to model
it for me, though.

07:43.900 --> 07:48.100
Conditions. I can't live
with all these conditions.

07:48.100 --> 07:49.260
Thanks.

07:52.140 --> 07:54.620
This is so unfair.
What?

07:54.620 --> 07:57.260
This is when things happen,
in the middle of the night,

07:57.260 --> 07:59.780
by which time I am completely
out of the scene.

07:59.780 --> 08:01.740
Life as a teenager.

08:01.740 --> 08:04.980
I just hate having to depend on
Lindsey to drive me everywhere.

08:04.980 --> 08:06.460
You'll be driving
before you know it.

08:06.460 --> 08:07.940
In the meantime,

08:07.940 --> 08:10.580
I missed Elizabeth Wurtzel
speaking at USC

08:10.580 --> 08:12.140
and the Goldfrapp concert.

08:12.140 --> 08:14.420
I was at the Goldfrapp
concert actually.

08:14.420 --> 08:16.660
Shut up. You were?
Mm-hmm.

08:16.660 --> 08:18.020
Was it great?

08:18.020 --> 08:20.060
Of course it was great.
What am I saying?

08:20.060 --> 08:22.220
Well, you could judge
for yourself.

08:22.220 --> 08:24.820
I got a bootleg MP3.
You have the concert?

08:24.820 --> 08:25.980
Just one song.

08:25.980 --> 08:28.700
A little louder, please,
so the authorities know.

08:28.700 --> 08:30.460
I totally have to hear it.

08:30.460 --> 08:31.540
I'll send it to you.

08:31.540 --> 08:35.059
After you get home,
after you get around to it.

08:36.100 --> 08:38.100
Good things are worth the wait.

08:38.100 --> 08:39.260
Oh....

08:39.260 --> 08:41.340
And what have you waited
for recently?

08:41.340 --> 08:43.980
I'm gonna have to wait
four years for you.

08:43.980 --> 08:46.940
You are just trying
to distract me from that MP3.

08:46.940 --> 08:48.460
Look, I have to send it.

08:48.460 --> 08:50.860
It's not like I could just
take you over to my house.

08:50.860 --> 08:53.620
That would be
a little insane.

08:53.620 --> 08:55.540
True.

08:55.540 --> 08:57.300
Okay, now don't peek.

08:58.220 --> 09:00.060
I shoot models for a living.

09:00.060 --> 09:01.780
I've seen it all before.

09:01.780 --> 09:03.620
And you're so sure about that?

09:03.620 --> 09:04.860
I'm thinkin' yeah.

09:04.860 --> 09:06.180
Maybe you should peek

09:06.180 --> 09:09.140
and make that clerk wonder
what's going on over here.

09:11.180 --> 09:13.100
In your dreams, little girl.

09:13.100 --> 09:14.620
Little girl?

09:14.620 --> 09:18.100
Whatever happened
to how mature I was?

09:20.020 --> 09:22.900
Is this mature enough for you?
Okay...

09:22.900 --> 09:25.940
Keep teasing me like that,
you're gonna drive me crazy.

09:25.940 --> 09:27.660
Is that so?

09:27.660 --> 09:29.340
Okay. All right.

09:32.500 --> 09:33.700
How's this?

09:33.700 --> 09:34.660
Nice.

09:36.500 --> 09:37.820
Okay.

09:37.820 --> 09:39.580
Now, there's three points
I have to make.

09:39.580 --> 09:42.020
One: you wouldn't take
advantage because

09:42.020 --> 09:44.260
you've been seen
with me here today.

09:44.260 --> 09:46.980
And two: it's Goldfrapp.

09:46.980 --> 09:49.260
And three?

09:49.260 --> 09:50.940
Well, and three--

09:50.940 --> 09:53.220
You said that it would
be insane for me

09:53.220 --> 09:55.780
to come over and...

09:55.780 --> 10:00.580
Four-- Four out of five doctors
agree that I am actually insane.

10:00.580 --> 10:03.340
Thus, I have to come over

10:03.340 --> 10:05.580
in order to be true to myself.

10:05.580 --> 10:07.860
Right?

10:21.780 --> 10:24.900
And the fourth reason:
this amazing car.

10:24.900 --> 10:27.260
Well, in the face
of logic like that,

10:27.260 --> 10:29.100
I bow down
and worship.

10:29.100 --> 10:30.180
Bow down?

10:31.460 --> 10:34.180
That's a good idea.
What are you waiting for?

10:34.180 --> 10:35.420
Worship me.

10:38.100 --> 10:40.340
Yes, oh, royal Thonggirl.

10:41.620 --> 10:43.700
I am not worthy
to kiss your feet.

10:44.980 --> 10:46.740
Well...maybe you are.

10:53.540 --> 10:55.660
Maybe we should,
like, get going.

10:57.940 --> 11:00.980
Yes, oh,
magnificent Thonggirl.

11:00.980 --> 11:05.300
You wanna call your sister?
Tell her where you'll be?

11:05.300 --> 11:07.700
Maybe later. I just wanna
get in this car.

12:07.620 --> 12:09.620
Wow. So hot.

12:14.700 --> 12:15.860
What's wrong?

12:15.860 --> 12:18.980
Well, they teach
us "young things"

12:18.980 --> 12:21.340
not to drink anything we haven't
mixed ourselves, so...

12:21.340 --> 12:22.980
Smart.

12:22.980 --> 12:25.164
Come back in the kitchen.
I'll pour it again.

12:25.190 --> 12:26.420
No.
Come on.

12:26.620 --> 12:29.260
I can whip up something
more entertaining than that.

12:38.140 --> 12:39.300
Oh...

12:39.300 --> 12:40.740
Healthy dude, huh?

12:40.740 --> 12:42.620
I try.

12:42.620 --> 12:44.900
Figure I'll live
as long as I can.

12:47.140 --> 12:48.980
Living long is overrated.

12:48.980 --> 12:51.540
What? You don't want
to reach a ripe, old age?

12:53.140 --> 12:55.380
For what?
When I'm 80?

12:55.380 --> 12:57.420
What do I do for fun?

12:57.420 --> 12:59.860
When you're 80 I'll be 98.

12:59.860 --> 13:02.660
Right... and useless to me.

13:03.860 --> 13:06.180
What use do you have
in mind for me?

13:16.700 --> 13:19.740
Ah. I knew there'd be
something fun around here.

13:26.180 --> 13:28.740
I bet these babes
got some dirt on you.

13:28.740 --> 13:30.100
Those are models.

13:30.100 --> 13:34.660
So why are they on your walls
instead of magazine covers?

13:36.100 --> 13:39.260
Here, looking at you while

13:39.260 --> 13:43.860
you know, you do
the most intimate things.

13:43.860 --> 13:45.860
My house is my studio.

13:45.860 --> 13:49.660
When clients come here, they're
walking into my giant portfolio.

13:49.660 --> 13:51.620
So, what?
These were all shot here?

13:55.220 --> 13:56.620
Oh, my God.

13:58.140 --> 14:00.860
Okay, you are like
a big deal, aren't you?

14:00.860 --> 14:03.220
I get work.

14:03.220 --> 14:07.380
Isn't that one of those cameras
that gives you the square image?

14:07.380 --> 14:08.740
How do you know that?

14:09.980 --> 14:13.460
I'm a goon. I just, like,
read constantly.

14:13.460 --> 14:15.620
You saw all those
books in my bag.

14:15.620 --> 14:17.340
You're not reading now.

14:18.340 --> 14:20.020
I'm not, am I?

14:24.260 --> 14:25.540
Feels good.

14:28.020 --> 14:29.940
Don't fall behind.

14:29.940 --> 14:31.340
We should toast.

14:33.540 --> 14:34.660
<i>Carpe...</i>

14:35.940 --> 14:37.780
<i>omnious.</i>

14:37.780 --> 14:39.380
What's that?

14:40.620 --> 14:42.860
It's my own little toast.

14:42.860 --> 14:44.500
You know <i>carpe diem.</i>

14:44.500 --> 14:45.660
"Seize the day."

14:45.660 --> 14:48.460
So I figure, <i>carpe omnious.</i>

14:48.460 --> 14:50.180
"Take it all."

14:51.460 --> 14:53.060
Take it all.

14:58.660 --> 15:00.220
So, like,

15:00.220 --> 15:03.660
what is it like to look through
your lens at some...

15:03.660 --> 15:06.300
beautiful woman
who's working so hard

15:06.300 --> 15:07.980
to look good for you?

15:07.980 --> 15:10.580
You know these models.
They all have handlers.

15:10.580 --> 15:13.140
People to make sure
their hair is just right

15:13.140 --> 15:14.580
and their makeup is okay

15:14.580 --> 15:17.660
and they don't get lost on
their way to their next gig.

15:17.660 --> 15:20.020
So you never get
to be alone with them?

15:20.020 --> 15:22.340
Rarely.
Poor Jeff.

15:22.340 --> 15:24.980
I am compensated for my
troubles. Don't worry about me.

15:24.980 --> 15:26.900
But I like worrying about you.

15:29.660 --> 15:32.060
It makes me wonder...

15:32.060 --> 15:32.980
What?

15:35.140 --> 15:36.980
No, no. Forget it.

15:36.980 --> 15:38.580
No, come on.

15:38.580 --> 15:41.220
Come on. What's in that
insane mind of yours?

15:46.580 --> 15:48.620
Okay. We'll have
another screwdriver

15:48.620 --> 15:50.740
and then maybe I'll tell you.

15:51.700 --> 15:55.460
I'm waiting.
Hold on.

15:55.460 --> 15:58.020
You are not keeping up.

16:03.580 --> 16:04.780
What?

16:04.780 --> 16:07.580
Here's where you're supposed
to make it easier for me

16:07.580 --> 16:09.060
and read my mind.

16:11.220 --> 16:13.700
You're wondering how many
models I've done it with.

16:16.100 --> 16:17.020
No.

16:19.100 --> 16:20.620
How many?
None of them.

16:20.620 --> 16:24.660
Oh, get out.
No. They're underage, mostly.

16:24.660 --> 16:26.060
I'd be arrested.

16:26.060 --> 16:28.060
So you're not arrested

16:28.060 --> 16:29.620
for photographing
them like this?

16:29.620 --> 16:32.140
I'm very aware
of the legal boundaries.

16:32.140 --> 16:33.900
I have to be.
Right. Right.

16:33.900 --> 16:37.260
'Cause secretly...
Secretly...

16:37.260 --> 16:39.460
you would like to do them.

16:39.460 --> 16:42.620
No. There's just one
that I slept with

16:42.620 --> 16:45.620
when we were both younger.

16:47.060 --> 16:48.060
That one?

16:48.060 --> 16:49.940
Not out here.

16:51.060 --> 16:53.940
In the bedroom?
No--

17:00.180 --> 17:02.180
What's her name?

17:02.180 --> 17:03.180
Hey.

17:03.180 --> 17:05.260
"Janelle."

17:05.260 --> 17:06.780
Yeah. Janelle.

17:08.740 --> 17:10.060
So, what? What?

17:10.060 --> 17:13.060
Was she, like, the first big
girlfriend or something?

17:13.060 --> 17:14.420
That's right.

17:15.579 --> 17:17.940
Learned everything I knew
practicing on her.

17:17.940 --> 17:19.619
And that date--

17:19.619 --> 17:23.099
Was that the first time
that you guys...

17:24.180 --> 17:25.660
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

17:29.820 --> 17:31.780
So, what? Where is she now?

17:31.780 --> 17:35.420
She actually signed with Ford
right after this shoot.

17:35.420 --> 17:38.500
She really took off. She, um...
Oh, my God.

17:38.500 --> 17:42.380
She is, like, on magazine
covers. I know her.

17:42.380 --> 17:44.940
Well, like, not personally,
obviously, but...

17:46.220 --> 17:48.100
You are impressive
every second.

17:48.100 --> 17:51.300
The models are impressive.
I just know how to bring it out.

17:52.420 --> 17:54.660
You still love her.

17:54.660 --> 17:55.860
No.

17:55.860 --> 17:57.180
Ah...yeah.

17:57.180 --> 17:58.180
No.
Yeah!

17:58.180 --> 17:59.420
No.
Really?

17:59.420 --> 18:00.780
No.
Really, really, really?

18:00.780 --> 18:01.820
No.

18:03.820 --> 18:06.500
I still love how simple things
were back then but...

18:06.500 --> 18:08.140
You know, I--

18:09.260 --> 18:11.700
I don't want to forget
that, but...

18:11.700 --> 18:13.100
we've moved on.

18:20.940 --> 18:22.740
You're lonely.

18:22.740 --> 18:24.340
No.

18:24.340 --> 18:26.740
I can hear it in your voice.

18:26.740 --> 18:28.260
I'm a big boy.

18:30.980 --> 18:34.620
I guess everyone kind of
has a Janelle, right?

18:34.620 --> 18:36.100
I guess.

18:37.860 --> 18:40.700
Hey. What if you got
one of your cameras

18:40.700 --> 18:43.580
and we can see what you
can bring out in me.

18:43.580 --> 18:45.820
This is what you wanted to ask?
Well, I--

18:45.820 --> 18:48.220
It's not as easy as you think.
Okay.

18:48.220 --> 18:50.460
Models don't just
pout their lips.

18:50.460 --> 18:52.740
They have to be willing
to open up.

18:52.740 --> 18:55.340
They have to show us
a little of their soul,

18:55.340 --> 18:57.500
their secrets.

18:57.500 --> 18:59.780
And most people only
open up from weakness.

18:59.780 --> 19:03.140
Nobody wants to see photos
of weak people.

19:03.140 --> 19:05.980
We look at great models
because they open up...

19:05.980 --> 19:07.620
from a position of...

19:09.020 --> 19:10.060
of, uh, of strength.

19:10.060 --> 19:12.020
They have the strength...

19:12.020 --> 19:13.820
to believe they
can do anything,

19:13.820 --> 19:17.180
no matter how crazy, or, uh...

19:17.180 --> 19:19.260
Are you okay?

19:19.260 --> 19:20.740
Uh...

19:21.660 --> 19:23.220
Let's try something.
Okay.

19:27.340 --> 19:29.660
Uh-uh. Do me out here.

19:30.820 --> 19:32.900
I shoot everyone in my studio.
Oh, come on.

19:36.020 --> 19:37.620
Clearly not.

19:41.180 --> 19:43.380
Come on, Jeff. Shoot me.

19:43.380 --> 19:44.980
Come on. Shoot me.

19:46.860 --> 19:48.380
Shoot me.

19:48.380 --> 19:50.580
Don't do that.
What?

19:50.580 --> 19:53.060
That phony music video crap.

19:53.060 --> 19:55.420
Come on.

19:55.420 --> 19:57.060
Just be yourself.

19:57.060 --> 19:59.380
Just be open.

19:59.380 --> 20:02.140
Weren't you just listening to me?
Come on, Jeff.

20:02.140 --> 20:02.980
Sit down. Shoot me.

20:03.006 --> 20:04.860
Look at me.

20:04.860 --> 20:06.180
Be honest.

20:07.380 --> 20:09.140
Would you listen to me?
Just sit down.

20:09.140 --> 20:10.500
Jeff, I don't--
Sit down.

20:10.500 --> 20:12.460
J-Jeff, I don't--
Sit down!

20:16.220 --> 20:17.340
Are you okay?

20:18.420 --> 20:20.580
I don't feel so good.

20:53.300 --> 20:55.380
Did you-- Did you call me?

20:56.940 --> 21:00.180
Sorry. I was just looking
through your medicine cabinet.

21:00.180 --> 21:03.700
Okay, boring! No <i>Valley of
the Dolls</i> stuff at all.

21:03.700 --> 21:07.220
Can't help but wondering
why all the lubricants though.

21:09.580 --> 21:13.340
Oh, hey, just--
Tell me when you're ready.

21:13.340 --> 21:14.700
Take your time.

21:18.220 --> 21:20.300
What did you...

21:20.300 --> 21:22.740
What di--
You remember what I said

21:22.740 --> 21:26.540
about not drinking anything
you didn't mix yourself?

21:27.620 --> 21:30.180
That's good advice
for everyone.

21:35.140 --> 21:37.780
You know what? I'm sorry
you were drugged for so long.

